ICFEP/ABAQUS-UQ

Consisting of:

Enriched experimental of design + Bayesian inference

clearvars; clc; close all;
 

Part 1: Setup

Directory setup

  • Set up working directory/input_file directory/output_file directory/subroutine directory
  • Set up UQLAB core directory
  • Set up working path (working path can be only under the file RUN)
%% Add UQlab core and subroutine directory
addpath("C:\Users\ny123\OneDrive - Imperial College London\PhD_Work\UQlab\UQLab_Rel2.0.0\UQLab_Rel2.0.0\core");%UQLAB core
addpath("C:\Users\ny123\OneDrive - Imperial College London\PhD_Work\SBI\Main\subroutines");%subroutine
 
% tell whether in the running folder
if ~contains(pwd(),caseInsensitivePattern('run'))
error('Working path is wrong!!!');
end
 
 
% define a working directory structrure for input/output
% decide whether reserve current FE results: true <-- delete; false <-- reserve
directory = Def_Dirs('true');
 
%% Initialize UQlab (not printing in the command window)
seed = 500;
rng(seed,'twister');
evalc('uqlab;');

Probabilistic input for EoD setup

%% Read input EoD parameters range from csv
Experimentaldesign = readtable([directory.inputcsv 'ExperimentalDesign.csv'], ...
TextType="string", VariableNamingRule="preserve");
ED = table2struct(Experimentaldesign);

Analysis parameters setup

  • Specify the number of seed/output fields/FE runs/Number of stage /enriched stage/parameters/percentage of training data over whole data
  • Create "AnParam" structure to store the analysis parameters.
AnParam.Name = cellstr(string({ED.Input_name}));
AnParam.FE_package = 'ICFEP';% choose FE package
AnParam.EoDseed = seed; %restore the seed
AnParam.N_outputfields = 2; %types of output sources
AnParam.N_RUN_EoD = 29; %number of FE runs required for EoD
AnParam.N_FE_stage = 70; %number of FE loading stages
AnParam.N_enrich = 71; %hope to enrich N_enrich-th stage for surrogate construction
% (1≤ AnParam.N_enrich ≤
% AnParam.N_FE_stage, if not in this range, no enrich)
AnParam.Switch_Predict = "on"; % switch for predictive posterior distribution for real outputs
AnParam.TrainDataPerc = 1; %range = (e.g., 0.8-0.9, ),slider to avoid unrealistic number
AnParam.N_parameters = size([ED.Input_name],2); % numbers of probabilistic input variables
AnParam.Switch_PCA_PCE_plot = "off"; % switch to show the PCA-PCE figures (test dataset against training dataset)
AnParam.Switch_PCA_Recon = "off"; % switch to show the PCA reconstruction error
AnParam.Switch_corner_scatter = "on"; % switch to show the posterior corner figures
AnParam.Switch_Sobol = "on"; % switch to show the posterior corner figures
AnParam.Switch_mv_st = "on"; % switch to show the posterior paramters mean and std with stages
AnParam.Switch_RMSE = "on"; % switch to show the posterior paramters mean and std with stages
AnParam.Trim = '1:60'; %Trim range
AnParam.Surrogate = "PCE"; % choices for surrogates
 
 
 
% Used in readoutput.m Very difficult to get rid of this as .m is hidden by UQlab.
if strcmp(AnParam.FE_package,'ICFEP')
%%% Define global variables
global FE_ID
FE_ID = 0;
end

UQlink setup

%% Wrapper ICFEP/ABAQUS with UQLink:
modelname = 'NonLinear_Truss';
filename = 'NonLinear_Truss';
switch AnParam.FE_package
case 'ABAQUS'
myUQLinkModel = ABAQUS_wrapper(modelname, filename);
case 'ICFEP'
myUQLinkModel = ICFEP_wrapper(modelname, filename);
end

Observation data setup

% if this is a systhetic problem, add Gaussian noise percentage
Noise.scalar = 0;% Value as a percentage (e.g. 0.01-1.0)
 
%% read observation (ground truth) data
[observationcoord,observationsarray,gtarray,Noise,observation_stageTime,AnParam] = readobservation(directory,Noise,AnParam);

Likelihood Gaussian discrepancy setup

%%Gaussian discrepancy error percentage related to observation in Bayesian
%%inversion (not considering modelling discrepancy, only for observation error)
scale_discrepancy{1} = 0.1; %(range 0.01~1)
scale_discrepancy{2} = 0.1; %(range 0.01~1)
 
%% Construct Gaussian discrepancy sigma^2 cell
for jj = 1:AnParam.N_outputfields
for kk = 1:AnParam.N_Obs_stage
sigma2{jj}(kk) = mean(observationsarray{jj}(:,kk),"all").*scale_discrepancy{jj};
%sigma2{jj}(kk) = max(abs(observationsarray{jj}(:,kk))).*scale_discrepancy{jj};
%sigma2{jj}(kk) = max(FEcell_output_interp{jj}{kk}(:,1))- min(FEcell_output_interp{jj}{kk}(:,1));
end
end

Part 2: EoD + Bayesian inference

2.2 Recursive inference

for jj = 1:AnParam.N_Obs_stage
 
 
% enrich EoD manually and extract enriched FE restults
if jj==1 %First stage EoD run
[~] = EnrichedFERun(myUQLinkModel,ED, AnParam,filename,directory,jj);
else
[~] = EnrichedFERun(myUQLinkModel,ED, AnParam,filename,directory,jj, Posterior);
end
 
% Merge different EoD results to EDarray/FEcell_output if possible
% Update the number of FE runs if possible
[coord, EDarray, FEcell_output,AnParam,FE_stageTime] = merge_EoD(AnParam);
 
 
%%since FE_stageTime and observation_stageTime are not consistant,
%%interpolation to make FE result to fit with observation
%%(FE_stageTime must contain observation_stageTime)
FEcell_output_interp = interpolation(observation_stageTime,FE_stageTime,FEcell_output, AnParam);
 
%% Trim coordination and FE results if possible (trim outputput 1)
[coord,FEcell_output_interp,observationsarray] = Trim(jj,AnParam,FEcell_output_interp, ...
coord,1,observationsarray);
 
%% Construct PCA-PCE for a given stage {jj-th stage}
[myPCE, PCA] = PCEPCA(AnParam, EDarray, FEcell_output_interp, jj);
 
%% Make PriorOpts/myPriorDist structure for parameter/discrepancy priors
%% Initial stage prior should be defined manually
 
if jj ==1
%intial srage prior should be defined manually
PriorOpts = []; Posterior{jj} = []; %initial empty cells
[PriorOpts, myPriorDist] = Dynamic_PriorOpts(ED,jj,AnParam, ...
observationsarray,sigma2,Posterior);
else
%rest stages should be inferred automatically
PriorOpts = []; %clear PriorOpts from last stage
[PriorOpts, myPriorDist] = Dynamic_PriorOpts(ED,jj,AnParam, ...
observationsarray,sigma2,Posterior);
end
 
%% === Observations ====
%%UQLAB doesnot support NAN in the myData.y
%%Repalce NAN with numerical value eplision=1e-20
epsilon = 1e-20;
for kk = 1:AnParam.N_outputfields
if ~isnan(observationsarray{kk}(:,jj))
obsconcat{kk} = observationsarray{kk}(:,jj)';
else
obsconcat{kk} = epsilon*ones(size(observationsarray{kk}(:,jj)))';
end
end
myData.y = obsconcat;
myData.Name = 'Multiple observations data sources';
% %% === Likelihood switch ====
myLogLikeli = likeliSwitch(jj,observationsarray,PCA,myPCE,AnParam);
 
%% Solver options: AIES MCMC
Solver.Type = 'MCMC';
%Solver.MCMC.Visualize.Parameters = 1:AnParam.N_parameters;
%Solver.MCMC.Visualize.Interval = 20;
Solver.MCMC.Sampler = 'AIES';
Solver.MCMC.Steps = 600;
Solver.MCMC.NChains = 25;
BayesOpts.Data = myData;
BayesOpts.Type = 'inversion';
BayesOpts.LogLikelihood = myLogLikeli;
BayesOpts.Solver = Solver;
BayesOpts.Prior = myPriorDist;
BayesAnalysis = uq_createAnalysis(BayesOpts);
 
%% response surface for RSM
[~] = RMSE_plotting(AnParam,jj,myPCE,PCA,EDarray,observationsarray,gtarray,Experimentaldesign,1e2);
 
 
%% sobol indices for plotting
[~] = Sobol_indices_plotting(AnParam, FEcell_output_interp,EDarray,jj,Experimentaldesign);
 
%% Postprocess (70% burn in; extract samples from posterior )
Posterior = BI_postprocess(jj,BayesAnalysis,AnParam,Posterior,gtarray,myPriorDist,Experimentaldesign);
 
%% plot paramter mv and st range with stages going
[~] = mv_st_GT_plotting(AnParam,Posterior, gtarray,jj,ED);
 
%% Predictive posterior
[~] = predictive_posterior(Posterior,AnParam,jj,EDarray,FEcell_output_interp,coord,observationsarray, gtarray);
 
 
end
